UADataType.Description: The MachineStateEnumType describes predefined states for a machine. This is a default state enumeration. It is possible to extend it for your project specific use-cases.

Field.Name: Clearing
Field.Description: The machine is in the time period between the release after an Emergency Stop by the operator and the resulting end state

Field.Name: Stopped
Field.Description: The machine has electrical power but is in a stationary state.

Field.Name: Starting
Field.Description: The machine is in production start. This is not to be confused with program Start up. An example might be the self-test of a packing robot, which tests the functionality of the individual servo motors through a movement test.

Field.Name: Idle
Field.Description: The machine is ready to carry out its intended function. It is however in a waiting state and must first be brought into operation by the operators or by external automatic release.

Field.Name: Suspended
Field.Description: Will be used in case of no detail status of suspended is needed

Field.Name: Execute
Field.Description: The machine is carrying out its intended function

Field.Name: Stopping
Field.Description: The machine is being transferred to the stopped state (Stopped) by a controlled stop routine.

Field.Name: Aborting
Field.Description: The machine is in the time period between the occurrence of the failure and the resulting end state (Emergency Stop).

Field.Name: Aborted
Field.Description: Machine is aborted and is not operating any more.

Field.Name: Holding
Field.Description: The machine is in the time period between the holding and the resulting end state (Held, Equipment Failure, External Failure).

Field.Name: Held
Field.Description: The machine is not carrying out its intended function due to an unpermitted deviation from the SET-state detected by a control system sensor.

Field.Name: Unholding
Field.Description: The machine is in the time period between the release of held (Held, Equipment Failure, External Failure) by the operator and the resulting end state (Operating).

Field.Name: Suspending
Field.Description: The machine is in the time period between the initiation of Suspending and the resulting end state (Prepared, Lack, Tailback, Lack Branch Line or Tailback Branch Line).

Field.Name: Unsuspending
Field.Description: The machine is in the time period between the release of being suspended (Prepared, Lack, Tailback, Lack Branch Line or Tailback Branch Line) and the resulting end state (Operating).

Field.Name: Resetting
Field.Description: The machine is in the time period between the release after a stop (Stopped) and the resulting end state (Idle).

Field.Name: Completing
Field.Description: Order quantity is going to reached.

Field.Name: Setup
Field.Description: Setup activities are performed on the machine.

Field.Name: EmergencyStop
Field.Description: The machine is in EmergencyStop state after operator hat pushed the emergency stop

Field.Name: HeldEquipmentFailure
Field.Description: Failure, which occurs in the machine itself and leads to a machine stop (in accordance with DIN 8782).

Field.Name: HeldExternalFailure
Field.Description: A failure which is not attributable to the machine but which nonetheless leads to a machine stop (in accordance with DIN 8782).

Field.Name: SuspendedPrepared
Field.Description: The machine is ready to carry out its intended function. However, it is in a waiting state which was not recognized as a lack or tailback state and can automatically start again.

Field.Name: SuspendedLack
Field.Description: The machine is not carrying out its intended function due to a lack detected by the sensor system in the inlet of the machine (Machine Stop).

Field.Name: SuspendedTailback
Field.Description: The machine is not carrying out its intended function due to a tailback detected by the sensor system in the outlet of the machine (Machine Stop).

Field.Name: SuspendedLackBranchLine
Field.Description: The machine is not carrying out its intended function due to a lack in the secondary inlet or a tailback in the secondary outlet of the machine (Machine Stop).

Field.Name: SuspendedTailbackBranchLine
Field.Description: The machine is not carrying out its intended function due to a lack in the secondary inlet or a tailback in the secondary outlet of the machine (Machine Stop).

UADataType.Description: The MachineModeEnumType describes predefined modes for a machine. This is a default mode enumeration. It is possible to extend it for your project specific use-cases.

Field.Name: Manual
Field.Description: This mode indicates that the machine is in manual mode. This feature may be used for the commissioning of the individual drives, verifying the operation of synchronized drives, testing the drive as result of modifying parameters, etc.

Field.Name: Maintenance
Field.Description: This mode indicates that the machine is in maintenance mode. This mode would typically be used for faultfinding, machine trials or testing operational improvements.

Field.Name: Automatic
Field.Description: The machine executes relevant logic in automatic mode. The machine is producing product or able to produce product.

Field.Name: SemiAutomatic
Field.Description: The machine executes relevant logic in semi-automatic mode. The machine is producing product or able to produce product where some operations are executed manually, while other operations are executed automatic.

Field.Name: Remote
Field.Description: The machine executes relevant logic in remote mode, e.g. it is controlled from a supervision control system.

Field.Name: StepMode
Field.Description: The machine executes relevant logic in step mode. This mode is typically used during commissioning where the machine processes a product step by step and the operator must start the next step manually.
